OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F317A1782807585
OL,3,CResident doctors vote to end strikes
OL,4,Cafter accepting government pay offer
OL,6,FResident doctors have accepted the
OL,7,Fgovernment's pay and jobs offer,
OL,8,Ffollowing a British Medical
OL,9,FAssociation (BMA) referendum in which
OL,10,Fthe majority voted in favour of the
OL,11,Fdeal.
OL,13,FThe deal will mean an average 6.6% pay
OL,14,Fuplift, to be fully implemented by
OL,15,FApril 2027.
OL,17,FDr Jack Fletcher, chairman of the
OL,18,FBMA's resident doctors committee
OL,19,F(RDC), said: "Resident doctors have
OL,20,Fspoken.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,318,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31702
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F317A1782807585
OL,3,CResident doctors vote to end strikes
OL,4,Cafter accepting government pay offer
OL,6,F"They have decided that the current
OL,7,Foffer is sufficient to continue on the
OL,8,Froad to pay restoration, and
OL,9,Fsufficient to address the absurd lack
OL,10,Fof jobs in the NHS. The strikes will
OL,11,Fnow end."
OL,13,FPlanned strikes for earlier this month
OL,14,Fhad been called off last minute by the
OL,15,FBMA's resident doctors committee after
OL,16,Fthe the government made their new
OL,17,Foffer, which was then put to and voted
OL,18,Fon by their members.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,318,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31703
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F317A1782807585
OL,3,CResident doctors vote to end strikes
OL,4,Cafter accepting government pay offer
OL,6,FThe referendum was held online between
OL,7,F18 - 26 June, and saw almost 33,000
OL,8,Fdoctors voting.
OL,10,FThere was a turnout of 57%, with 53%
OL,11,Fof eligible BMA members voting in
OL,12,Ffavour of the government proposal.
OL,14,FThe June strike action had been
OL,15,Fscheduled to take place 15 ` 19, and
OL,16,Fthe four-day walkout would have been
OL,17,Fthe 16th round of strike action since
OL,18,F2023. Since July 2025, there have been
OL,19,F21 days of strikes by the BMA.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
