CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F317A1782807585
OL,3,CResident doctors vote to end strikes
OL,4,Cafter accepting government pay offer
OL,6,FIn response to the referendum result,
OL,7,FHealth Secretary James Murray said:
OL,8,F"This is very good news for resident
OL,9,Fdoctors, patients and the NHS as a
OL,10,Fwhole, allowing us to draw a line
OL,11,Funder the disruption of previous
OL,12,Fmonths and focus on getting on with
OL,13,Fthe job of rebuilding our health
OL,14,Fservice".
OL,16,FHe added that resident doctors will
OL,17,Fbenefit from a "new pay structure" and
OL,18,F"better career progression" in a
OL,19,F"period of greater stability" for the
OL,20,FNHS.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,318,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31708
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F317A1782807585
OL,3,CResident doctors vote to end strikes
OL,4,Cafter accepting government pay offer
OL,6,F"But this is the beginning, not the
OL,7,Fend of the journey. I know there is
OL,8,Fmuch more to do, and I am determined
OL,9,Fto keep working constructively with
OL,10,Fresident doctors, all NHS staff, and
OL,11,Fthe unions who represent them to
OL,12,Fimprove their working lives and
OL,13,Ftogether build a health service that
OL,14,Fis fit for the future", he added.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/8
